DURBAN - Protesters complaining about access to water and ablution facilities blocked traffic on the M4 highway by burning tyres at the Clairwood/Jacobs offramp yesterday[Sunday].
 Mpumelelo Zuma, the ward 32 Clairwood councillor said around 200 people from an informal settlement serviced by eThekwini Municipality protested over the relocation of a “stand water pipe.”

 He said the water pipe was centrally placed for 10 years but has now been relocated to the New York informal settlement in Archery Road.
"The people living at the new location of the pipe are depriving the others of using the water pipe,” he said.
 Zuma said the people want to know why the pipe was moved?

 






