He said another issue is that some people are also being deprived of using the ablution facilities that are located in the New York settlement.
 “They are forced to relieve themselves in the bushes and are being attacked and robbed by vagrants,” said Zuma.
 Zuma said some people are being given preferential treatment while others are suffering.

 “Some people are being favoured by officials while some are being deprived and everyone should be getting the same treatment,” he said.
 He said five people were arrested and sustained several injuries to their faces, arms and legs.
Police did not respond to a request for comment.

THE MERCURY